overview:
Phoebe Farber is currently a Senior at Northeastern University and is studying Business Administration, concentrating in Entrepreneurship with minors in Psychology and Organizational Leadership Studies.

When she was younger she worked with marketing in her martial arts school, working on lead generation and daily operations. She was a member of the Future Business Leaders of America for four years and a state officer in NY for two years and has currently serves as the President of the Alumni Association. In 2009, FBLA named her Ms. Future Business Leader and she won 1st place in the Business Ethics competition. She has a passion for entrepreneurship and real estate and hopes to pursue both in the future.
